{
  "texts": [
    "We removed duplicated reads with SAMtools [88] and called variable sites using BCFtools [89].",
    "We only used reads with mapping-and base-quality ≥ 20 in the variant calling.",
    "The variant calls were then filtered to only keep biallelic SNPs with the following requirements: site-and genotype-quality ≥ 20, read coverage ≥ 6, < 20% missing data, and minor allele frequency > 0.05.We used population branch statistics (PBS) [90] to estimate the genetic differentiation of lineages leading into the resistant genotypes of each population.",
    "Standard differentiation measures, such as F ST or d XY, can detect signals of differential selection, but they generally cannot distinguish which of the populations has been the target of selection.",
    "To detect lineage-specific selection, PBS uses an outgroup to polarize differentiation measures between two closely related populations."
  ]
}